{%- doc -%}
  For collection pages: picks a variant when Variant SKU ends with a Theme Code (suffix match).
  Shopify collection handles are hyphenated (e.g. peppermint, candy, specials).

  Routing (Country Silk):
  - Specials: all Christmas / palette themes share one collection URL; first SKU suffix match wins using the ordered code list below.
  - Peppermint: handle or title contains "peppermint" (no "Christmas" in collection name) → RW2.
  - Candy: hyphenated handle contains "candy" (e.g. candy, candy-…), or collection title is exactly "candy" → CND.

  Theme table (Theme Code = last 3 characters of Variant SKU):
  | # | Theme Name            | Code |
  |---|------------------------|------|
  | 18 | Peppermint            | RW2  |
  | 19 | Candy                 | CND  |
  | 23 | Traditional Christmas | TR2 (TRA alternate in list) |
  | 34 | Cozy Christmas        | BR2  |
  | 49 | Enchanted Christmas   | BSW  |
  | 51 | Ruby Red Christmas    | RRD  |
  | 52 | Festive Christmas     | FAS  |

  Specials list order: Christmas themes by table, then other palette codes still used on that collection.

  Outputs variant id or empty.

  @param {object} product - Product
  @param {object} collection - Current collection
{%- enddoc -%}
{%- liquid
  assign pick_id = ''
  assign ch = collection.handle | downcase | strip
  assign ct = collection.title | downcase | strip
  assign codes_line = ''

  comment
    Specials = single URL for Traditional, Cozy, Enchanted, Ruby Red, Festive, Emerald, Gold/Silver/Red-White, etc.
    Order: try each code in sequence; first variant with matching SKU suffix wins.
  endcomment
  if ch == 'specials' or ch == 'special-offers' or ct == 'specials' or ch contains 'specials'
    assign codes_line = 'TR2,TRA,BR2,BSW,RRD,FAS,EMR,GD2,SWC,RRW2,RRW,GWN,GLD,BRW,PGW,RSC,BUF'
  elsif ch contains 'peppermint' or ct contains 'peppermint'
    assign codes_line = 'RW2'
  elsif ch contains 'candy' or ct == 'candy'
    assign codes_line = 'CND'
  endif

  if codes_line != blank
    assign code_parts = codes_line | split: ','
    for code_token in code_parts
      if pick_id != blank
        break
      endif
      assign code_u = code_token | strip | upcase
      if code_u == blank
        continue
      endif
      assign csize = code_u.size
      for variant in product.variants
        if pick_id != blank
          break
        endif
        assign sku_raw = variant.sku | strip
        if sku_raw == blank
          continue
        endif
        assign sku_u = sku_raw | upcase
        assign ssize = sku_u.size
        if ssize >= csize
          assign start_i = ssize | minus: csize
          assign suf = sku_u | slice: start_i, csize
          if suf == code_u
            assign pick_id = variant.id
            break
          endif
        endif
      endfor
    endfor
  endif
-%}
{{- pick_id -}}
